This article discusses an executive order issued by President Joseph R. Biden Jr. regarding the apportionment of congressional representatives based on the population count from the decennial census. The order revokes previous policies that aimed to exclude individuals without lawful immigration status from the apportionment base. The order emphasizes that the Constitution and existing laws require the inclusion of all persons residing in each state, regardless of their immigration status, in the apportionment base. It also highlights the importance of accurate and reliable census data. The order does not affect the authority of executive departments or agencies or the functions of the Director of the Office of Management and Budget.